    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-04-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-04-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="394"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d394">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 594/36–37.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Gummeré</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-04-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 181.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    unnumbered dispatch of the 20th ultimo transmitting the reply of Sid Mohamed ben
                    Guebbass to your letter of the 15th of the same month in regard to the desire of
                    certain American missionaries to obtain a house in the Moorish quarter of
                    Mequinez.</p>
                <p>Ben Guebbass should be urged to make clear to His Majesty the importance this
                    Government attaches to the fulfilment of the Moorish promise.</p>
                <p>Awaiting something more definite,</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
